The k-mer analyzer script analyzes a DNA sequence to find the total counts of each k-mer in the sequence, and the total counts of each "next character", the character that comes immediately after that k-mer. 
To run the script, the user must input/type the name of the script(kmer_analyzer.py), the input and output text file names, and the k value. The input file should contain the DNA sequence the user would like to analyze, the output text file is where the results will be written, and k is the user specified length of the k-mer.
After running, the script output a file that contains the total frequency for each k-mer and the frequency of the next characters, given a user-specified value of k. The results are written in the format : k-mer(total count): character:frequency, character:frequency.
